[div class=p 
	[em 
		"Daedalian Opus
	]em
	" is an early puzzle game for the Game Boy where the player must solve jigsaw puzzles with pentominoes (5-block shapes instead of the familiar 4-block tetromino). The player is awarded new pieces to use periodically to help with the more complex later levels.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/Jigwally 
		"Jigwally
	]a
	" solves this game's puzzles with custom software that employs the 
	[a href=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dancing_Links rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Dancing Links
	]a
	" algorithm to find 
	[a href=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exact_cover rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"exact covers
	]a
	" (solutions) for each jigsaw. The author analyzed and chose the overall fastest solution for each puzzle, and completed the game in record time.
	$LF
]div
